Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.17,0:00:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Get--get over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.18,0:00:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Tents are lookin' good.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.85,0:00:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And we made good time today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.48,0:00:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, we'll be at\NWinsome Falls by tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.35,0:00:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We should do the annual big\Nsister little sister
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.72,0:00:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,camping trip every weekend!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.12,0:00:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it wouldn't be annual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.06,0:00:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we did it\Nevery weekend,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.66,0:00:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it probably wouldn't\Nbe as special.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.76,0:00:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But the more we do it, the\Nbetter we get at camping!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.03,0:00:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the first\Ntime we came here
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.53,0:00:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and Rarity had that\Ngi-normous tent?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.90,0:00:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.81,0:00:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gotten much better at\Nroughing it, haven't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.14,0:00:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup. This time you only\Npacked three suitcases!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.18,0:00:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you're\Nthinking, but I promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.55,0:00:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I only brought\Nthe essentials.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.79,0:00:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Like those light thingies?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.56,0:00:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.39,0:00:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What is life if you\Ncan't make it beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.56,0:01:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm. These berries look\Ngood enough to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.03,0:01:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,DON'T!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.20,0:01:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,According to my book, they're\Nextremely poisonous!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.71,0:01:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.71,0:01:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard something; I\Nstepped on something
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.02,0:01:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw that\Ncreepy cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.79,0:01:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I still get\Na little bit scared out here,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.49,0:01:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,even after the\Nlast camping trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.82,0:01:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, kid, you've\Ngot a big sister this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.77,0:01:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Bloom: This looks amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.84,0:01:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to be the best\Nbig sister/little sister
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.37,0:01:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,camping trip ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.95,0:01:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Aaaahhhhhh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.56,0:02:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow! What are these things!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.80,0:02:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Aaahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly-ders!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.57,0:02:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Everypony run for cover!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.57,0:02:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get stuck\Nin their...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.71,0:02:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,...web!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.38,0:02:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh! Now what!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.95,0:02:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow me, everypony!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.49,0:03:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Scootaloo: Agh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.75,0:03:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the scary cave!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.63,0:03:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did those\Nterrible bugs come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And why did they\Ndestroy our camp?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.36,0:03:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly-ders are from\Nthe Luna Bay Area.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.73,0:03:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Never seen 'em this\Nfar east though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.93,0:03:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably attracted\Nto the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.74,0:03:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Best wait here\Nuntil they're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.44,0:03:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, apple rot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.11,0:03:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we supposed to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.01,0:03:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We had games to play and\Nmarshmallows to roast at camp!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.08,0:03:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In here we got nothin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.51,0:03:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not entirely true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.65,0:03:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We have each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.42,0:03:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.72,0:03:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you girls want to,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.95,0:03:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe we could tell some stories
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.66,0:03:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to pass the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.89,0:03:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Rainbow: You want stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.56,0:03:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a ton of stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.69,0:03:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Spoiler Alert: they're all\Nabout me and how awesome I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.00,0:03:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking more\Nlike campfire stories...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.93,0:03:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't even\Nhave a campfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.50,0:03:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I got this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.54,0:04:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. That was brave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.48,0:04:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh, it was no biggie..
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.98,0:04:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We aren't gonna\Ntell scary stories
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.65,0:04:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,like our last camping\Ntrip, are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.29,0:04:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's bad enough\Njust being in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.75,0:04:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Scootaloo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.15,0:04:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna tell you mine and\NApple Bloom's favorite legend!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.59,0:04:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! You mean Rockhoof?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.26,0:04:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I love that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.80,0:04:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He was so strong and when he...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.10,0:04:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple Bloom! Shhh. We\Nhaven't heard it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.83,0:04:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.10,0:04:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.84,0:04:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.07,0:04:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Rockhoof was known far and wide\Nfor his incredible strength
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.61,0:04:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but he didn't start\Nout that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.68,0:04:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Rockhoof was\Na tiny little fella,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.75,0:04:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the son of a farmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.95,0:04:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.81,0:04:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh heh heh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.92,0:04:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They lived in a village\Nthat sat at the foot
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.29,0:04:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of a gigantic volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.39,0:04:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And the village was protected by{\i0}\N{\i1} an elite group of Guard Ponies{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:04:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} called the Mighty Helm.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.10,0:04:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.97,0:05:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Young Rockhoof wanted nothing{\i0}\N{\i1} more than to be part{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.67,0:05:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} of the Mighty Helm...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.01,0:05:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha ha ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.48,0:05:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ...but he was told that{\i0}\N{\i1} he was too scrawny{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} and weak to protect{\i0}\N{\i1} the village.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.49,0:05:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But Rockhoof wouldn't{\i0}\N{\i1} take "no" for an answer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.63,0:05:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Then one fateful day...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.83,0:05:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} The volcano erupted!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.37,0:05:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeeeeeeee!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.61,0:05:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my favorite part!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.31,0:05:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All: What happened next!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.34,0:05:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The molten lava poured down\Nthe side of the volcano...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.42,0:05:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ... and try as they might, the{\i0}\N{\i1}Mighty Helm couldn't figure out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.39,0:05:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} a way to save the village.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.86,0:05:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} They had to evacuate.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.69,0:05:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But the village ponies didn't{\i0}\N{\i1} want to leave their homes!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.79,0:06:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} They spent their{\i0}\N{\i1} entire lives there.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.76,0:06:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} They had nowhere else to go!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.10,0:06:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} So Rockhoof decided{\i0}\N{\i1} to do something crazy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.91,0:06:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} He thought if he could{\i0}\N{\i1} divert the flow of the lava,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.65,0:06:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} he might be able to{\i0}\N{\i1} save his village!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.52,0:06:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} He started digging a trench.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.02,0:06:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Sweetie Belle: Wait a minute...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.82,0:06:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All by himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.59,0:06:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be impossible for one pony\Nto dig a trench fast enough
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.39,0:06:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop the lava!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.73,0:06:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, even I couldn't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.03,0:06:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing Rockhoof\Ndidn't believe
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.97,0:06:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in the word "impossible".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.27,0:06:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} He continued to work, knowing{\i0}\N{\i1} the odds were against him{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.84,0:06:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but determined to push through.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.88,0:06:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Then... something{\i0}\N{\i1} magical happened.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.95,0:07:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Rockhoof got visibly stronger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.99,0:07:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But the lava was{\i0}\N{\i1} getting closer...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.55,0:07:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Through his extraordinary{\i0}\N{\i1} determination{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.22,0:07:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} and sheer force of will,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.12,0:07:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Rockhoof more than earned{\i0}\N{\i1} his place in the Mighty Helm.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.99,0:07:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.96,0:07:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Good story,\NApplejack!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.96,0:07:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it\Nwasn't about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.00,0:07:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I love that story, no matter\Nhow many times I hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.53,0:07:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we see if it's\Nsafe to head back to camp?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.84,0:07:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Sweetie Belle: Uh, girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.77,0:07:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no camp to go back to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.18,0:08:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All our hard work is ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.92,0:08:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There, there. Sweetie Belle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.49,0:08:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.86,0:08:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How? Our camp was so pretty and\Nthis cave is sooo...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.33,0:08:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,...not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.23,0:08:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, nononono no, not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.87,0:08:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's beauty in everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Even these blah rocks\Naren't really blah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.41,0:08:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look closely, you can\Nsee flecks of gold in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.58,0:08:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way the firelight\Ndances on the cave wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.81,0:08:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,shadow and light!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.78,0:08:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooooh, it's so gorgeous!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.55,0:08:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sweetie Belle, have I ever told\Nyou about{\i1} my{\i0} favorite legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.02,0:08:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I didn't know you had one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.32,0:08:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name was Mistmane.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.99,0:08:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistmane?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.70,0:08:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't she the old wrinkly\Nsorceress with the flower?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.23,0:08:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But did you\Nknow she used to be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.94,0:08:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the most beautiful\Nunicorn in all the land?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.34,0:09:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.61,0:09:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happened to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.38,0:09:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Mistmane was a very\Npromising young sorceress.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.65,0:09:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} She was as talented as she{\i0}\N{\i1} was beautiful and kind.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.85,0:09:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Everypony loved her{\i0}\N{\i1} and missed her{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} when she was sent to the{\i0}\N{\i1} finest magic school.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.93,0:09:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} While she was gone, she was{\i0}\N{\i1} delighted to find out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.83,0:09:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} that her best friend, Sable{\i0}\N{\i1} Spirit, was crowned Empress.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.41,0:09:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She couldn't wait to return home{\i0}\N{\i1} once she finished her studies.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But once she arrived, she was{\i0}\N{\i1} devastated by what she saw.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.95,0:09:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.82,0:09:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Empress happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.79,0:09:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She makes everypony work\Nday and night on her palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.29,0:09:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have time to take\Ncare of anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.80,0:09:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that can't be. I know her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.23,0:09:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She would never do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.10,0:10:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But there was no denying{\i0}\N{\i1} what was in front of her.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.48,0:10:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Sable Spirit took everything{\i0}\N{\i1} that was beautiful{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.98,0:10:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} away from anypony else.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.42,0:10:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But Mistmane was sure there{\i0}\N{\i1} had to be some explanation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.02,0:10:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd assume there was\Ntoo, if somepony told me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.82,0:10:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,either one of you\Ntwo'd gone evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.93,0:10:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'd never believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.96,0:10:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.90,0:10:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen the way you two\Nget when you miss breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.30,0:10:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha! Just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.80,0:10:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'd want answers, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.67,0:10:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So did Mistmane.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.30,0:10:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,She went to confront her friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.68,0:10:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Sable? Is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.88,0:10:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you don't\Nrecognize your old friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.28,0:10:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't. My friend would never\Nwork our families and friends
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.65,0:10:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to the bone for something\Nas silly as a palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.52,0:11:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Silly? My palace is\Na beacon of beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.36,0:11:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anypony who passes will\Nbe in awe of its majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.47,0:11:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What good is a pretty palace if\Nit just hides the misery
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.87,0:11:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of its ponies?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.47,0:11:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty is everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.97,0:11:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You taught me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.74,0:11:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.71,0:11:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You were always\Nthe pretty one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.61,0:11:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to go to the\Nbest magic school.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.11,0:11:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everypony missed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.85,0:11:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everypony loved you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.78,0:11:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I admit, I was jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.95,0:11:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tried to perform a spell\Nthat would make me beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.56,0:11:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see how{\i1} that{\i0} went.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.83,0:11:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I vowed if I couldn't have\Nbeauty, I would take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.63,0:11:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't chosen to\Nbe Empress, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.33,0:11:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I took it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.07,0:11:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like I'm going to\Ntake everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.24,0:11:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistmane: I can't\Nlet you do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.34,0:11:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me? [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.48,0:12:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.48,0:12:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Rarity: Everypony thought{\i0}\N{\i1} Sable Spirit was defeated{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.09,0:12:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} and that was that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.62,0:12:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But Mistmane knew there was{\i0}\N{\i1} more she could do to help.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.36,0:12:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Beauty isn't everything, but{\i0}\N{\i1}Mistmane knew that it does have{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the power to make ponies smile.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} She made a huge sacrifice to{\i0}\N{\i1} bring that smile back{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.34,0:12:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} to her friends' and{\i0}\N{\i1} families' faces.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.78,0:12:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Including Sable Spirit's.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.72,0:13:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You did this for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.65,0:13:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after I was so cruel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.49,0:13:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Sable Spirit was so touched{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.66,0:13:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} that she vowed to be{\i0}\N{\i1} more like her friend{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.46,0:13:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} in the ways that mattered.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} From then on, she ruled with{\i0}\N{\i1} kindness and compassion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.81,0:13:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Even though she gave{\i0}\N{\i1} away her physical beauty,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.48,0:13:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} she dedicated her life to{\i0}\N{\i1} spreading beauty{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.68,0:13:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} all over Equestria.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.22,0:13:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Anytime you go out of your way{\i0}\N{\i1} to brighten somepony's day{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.26,0:13:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} by doing something nice{\i0}\N{\i1} like giving them flowers,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.89,0:13:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you're following in the\Nhoofsteps of Mistmane.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.70,0:13:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she's my\Nfavorite legend, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahhh!!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.08,0:14:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.11,0:14:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These Fly-ders won't quit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.18,0:14:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they want from us now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.98,0:14:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like it or\Nnot, we're food too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.28,0:14:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've got the\Nbites to prove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.22,0:14:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we going to do!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.45,0:14:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They're almost here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.43,0:14:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.46,0:14:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now those bugs can't get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.47,0:14:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And{\i1} we{\i0} can't get{\i1} out{\i0} !
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.90,0:14:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.58,0:14:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all just stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.58,0:14:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Lemme re-light this fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.42,0:14:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have to wait\Nuntil the swarm moves on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.22,0:14:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll think of a way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.79,0:14:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,How long will\Nthat be!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.22,0:14:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bears live in caves!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.93,0:14:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.73,0:14:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Scootaloo, you're focusing\Non the wrong things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.66,0:14:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a plan!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.93,0:14:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Close.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.80,0:15:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a story!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me guess,\Nit's about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.77,0:15:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Practically.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.27,0:15:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about{\i1} my{\i0} favorite\Nlegend, Flash Magnus.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.64,0:15:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't he the pony who\Ntook on the Dragons?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.15,0:15:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragons!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.18,0:15:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Big, scary mean\Nones or like Spike?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.38,0:15:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, these were definitely\Nthe big scary mean kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.72,0:15:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But not too scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.03,0:15:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can sit closer\Nto me if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.80,0:15:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A long time ago, before the\NWonderbolts were even founded,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.87,0:15:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Flash Magnus was a lowly\Ncadet in the Royal Legion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.24,0:15:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Legion needed to\Nfly over the Dragon Lands
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.21,0:15:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to their comrades\Non the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.85,0:15:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But as they got closer\Nto the Dragons...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.39,0:15:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,... The Dragons attacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.69,0:15:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You said this wasn't too scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.19,0:16:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[muffled] Scootaloo, if you\Njust hang in there...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.66,0:16:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.93,0:16:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, if you\Njust hang in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.03,0:16:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise you'll\Nlike the ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.07,0:16:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, like I way saying, Flash\NMagnus and the Royal Legion
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.97,0:16:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,tried to get past the dragons...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.88,0:16:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} ... but the Dragons{\i0}\N{\i1} wouldn't let them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.78,0:16:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Everypony, RETREAT!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.95,0:16:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Flash Magnus and a few other{\i0}\N{\i1} cadets were separated{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.29,0:16:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} from the battalion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.76,0:16:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} He managed to get away but the{\i0}\N{\i1} dragons captured his friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.86,0:16:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} and took them back{\i0}\N{\i1} to their lair.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.94,0:16:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.85,0:16:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to save our\Ncaptured comrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.02,0:16:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate your\Nloyalty, Flash Magnus,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.55,0:17:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but getting past those dragons\Nis going to be impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.59,0:17:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing will work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.62,0:17:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Apple Bloom: The Commander was right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.29,0:17:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't\Nout-fight Dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.49,0:17:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can out-think them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.90,0:17:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander Ironhead, I'm pretty\Nsure I can out-fly the Dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.24,0:17:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can lure them\Ninto chasing me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.04,0:17:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you can all sneak into the\Nlair and retrieve our friends
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.31,0:17:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,before they get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.68,0:17:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really willing to\Ntake that chance, Soldier?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.08,0:17:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I am, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.02,0:17:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very brave\Nthing you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.45,0:17:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll need all the\Nhelp you can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.79,0:17:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this... Netitus?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.99,0:17:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The fireproof shield?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.26,0:17:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It has protected legion\Nheroes for generations
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.00,0:17:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and today I can't think\Nof a worthier flank
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.90,0:17:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for Netitus to protect!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.74,0:17:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck, soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.53,0:17:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew..
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.31,0:18:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Come and get me,\Nfire breath! If you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey! Come and get me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.62,0:18:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! I'm over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.93,0:18:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} While Flash Magnus{\i0}\N{\i1} bravely flew for his life,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.93,0:18:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Commander Ironhead was able{\i0}\N{\i1} to get his soldiers back.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.87,0:18:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Flash Magnus flew like the wind.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.07,0:18:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Faster than the dragons!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.81,0:18:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} But he knew he couldn't{\i0}\N{\i1} do this forever.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Luckily, he had a plan.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.83,0:18:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} He led the dragons{\i0}\N{\i1} straight into a storm{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.34,0:18:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} that the Legion had planted.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.64,0:19:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} One taste of the lightning{\i0}\N{\i1} and the dragons retreated!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1} Flash Magnus' plan worked!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.27,0:19:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Scootaloo: Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.93,0:19:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I did like that ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.74,0:19:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Told ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.74,0:19:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He always inspired me to be\Nmy brave and awesome self.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.64,0:19:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmhmm!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.51,0:19:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I guess he kinda\Nreminds me of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.51,0:19:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.85,0:19:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.81,0:19:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.89,0:19:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, d'you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.92,0:19:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.. I don't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.39,0:19:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.63,0:19:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Those gosh darn\Nfly-ders are gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.03,0:19:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We can get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.53,0:19:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.53,0:20:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.74,0:20:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna have to see if we\Ncan get out the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean go further into\Nthe dark, spooky cave?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.24,0:20:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Scootaloo, just\Nremember the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.01,0:20:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotta be brave like\Nme and Flash Magnus. OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.22,0:20:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear water!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.29,0:20:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's\Nflowing water, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.22,0:20:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It might lead to the way out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.79,0:20:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ohhh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.49,0:20:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,OK on three!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.86,0:20:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.83,0:20:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.90,0:20:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,THREE!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.24,0:20:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Woohoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.21,0:20:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.48,0:20:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, whaddaya know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.11,0:20:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We found ourselves a\Nshortcut to Winsome Falls!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.42,0:20:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Scootaloo: Oh.. It's never\Nlooked so beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.15,0:20:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, almost...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.96,0:21:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We sure are sorry\Nthat our camping trip
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.73,0:21:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't what we\Nhoped it would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.30,0:21:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.43,0:21:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This trip is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.17,0:21:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It is?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.23,0:21:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We got to hear legendary stories\Nand go on an adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.21,0:21:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, you three want to stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we do!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.08,0:21:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We could turn those trees\Ninto a nice little shelter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.41,0:21:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We can get you some big logs\Nand branches to help build it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.35,0:21:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And I bet we can find\Nsome more berries.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.85,0:21:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.92,0:21:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooo.. I can't wait to see\Nwhat happens next year!
